										<div class="modal-sidebar">
											<h4><u>Need help measuring?</u></h4>
										</div>
										<p>When ordering a mattress with a special corner cut (Radius, Angled, or Notched), there are 2 boxes per corner that require measurement entry. These measurements represent the distance being removed from the corner being cut off, along each side.</p>
										<p>Sometimes it's hard to know what that measurement is, so here is an easy way to get it</p>
										<p><span class="text-uppercase"><u>Example:</u></span><br>
										If the overall dimensions of your mattress were 60" x 74", and you had a special cut corner (radius, angle, or notch) at the foot of the mattress, you would need to enter 2 measurements for that corner.</p>
										<p>If you measured from the head of the mattress, down to where the special corner (radius, angle, or notch) starts, and that measurement was 59", then you would enter 15" in the box for that side (74" - 59" = 15").</p>
										<p>Repeat the process for the other box. For example, if you measured from the side of the mattress to where the special corner cut starts, and you measured 53", then you would enter 7" in the required box (60" - 53" = 7").</p><img src="/wp-content/uploads/notch.png">
										<p>If you still have questions, please feel free to call us at <a data-ctm-tracked="1" data-ctm-watch-id="1" href="tel:+18886901081">888-690-1081</a> (Mon-Fri, 8am-4pm PST) and we'd be happy to help!</p>
